Mediterranean Lentil Salad with Feta and Mint
  --Stephanie McKercher, RDN
  
Dressing:
1/4 c evoo
2 tbsp lemon juice
1 tbsp dijon mustard
1 clove garlic, minced
1 tsp dry oregano
1/4 tsp salt (to taste)
1/9 tsp pepper (to taste)

whisk all ingredients until evenly mixed. Set aside.

Salad:
2 1/2 c cooked brown lentils
1 red bell pepper, diced
1 c quartered cherry tomatoes
1 c diced cucumber
1/3 c minced red onion
1/3 c chopped walnuts (optional)
1/3 c chopped kalamata olives (optional)
1/4 c chopped fresh parsley
2 tbsp torn mint leaves
2 tbsp torn fresh dill
1 c crumbled feta

Stir cooked lentils, bell pepper, tomatoes, cucumber, onion, walnuts (if using), olives (if using), parsley, mint, and dill. Pour dressing over mixture and stir until evenly coated. Add feta cheese and gently toss until evenly mixed.


Notes: 1 c dry lentils == 2 1/2 c cooked. If using canned, drain and rinse first. Any color lentils will work. Can prep deressing up to 2 weeks in advance and salad up to 5 days in advance. Salad can be stored in air tight container up to 5 days in fridge and freezer for up to 3 months.
cooking lentils: cook 1 c in 3 1/2 c water, simmering over low-medium heat for 20 min. Drain excess liquid. 


